modules.description: The module offers SQL code generation, parsing, and syntax extensions for PostgreSQL integration, operating on database connections, OCaml ASTs, and type information. It enables handling SQL queries, type conversions, and connection management while enforcing specific syntax patterns for database interactions and object mappings.

Provides functions to establish database connections, execute parameterized SQL queries, and retrieve results as structured records. Works with types such as connection handles, query parameters, and result sets containing typed fields. Used to dynamically generate and run complex database operations in applications requiring real-time data interaction.

Generates and parses SQL code with PostgreSQL-specific syntax, operating on OCaml ASTs and type information to enable seamless database interactions. It supports query construction, type conversion, and connection management through custom syntax extensions. Users can define database schemas, map OCaml types to SQL tables, and execute parameterized queries. Examples include generating type-safe query functions and automating schema migrations.
